-- Biosensors says CITIC PE unit won't proceed with takeover 
-- By Rujun Shen
-- Tue Aug 19, 2014 05:47AM EDT
-- None



SINGAPORE, Aug 19 (Reuters) - Biosensors International Ltd <BIOS.SI> said on Tuesday that a private equity unit of CITIC Group [CITIC.UL] has decided not to proceed with its takeover bid of the company.

CITIC Private Equity Funds Management Co., Ltd was reported to be in talks to take over the entire stake of Biosensors, a medical equipment maker with headquarters in Singapore. [ID:nL3N0LO0LQ] "CITIC Private Equity Funds Management Co., Ltd. has informed the company that it has decided not to proceed with any takeover transactions involving the shares in the company at this point of time," Biosensors said in a statement. [ID:nSNZ1CLRYP] CITIC PE already holds an indirect stake of 21.80 percent in the company and is its largest shareholder.